@page
@model AboutModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About this Demo Application";
}
<div class="card h-100 shadow">
    <img class="card-img" src="~/images/bg_homepage.jpg" style="height:auto"/> 
    <div class="card-img-overlay">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h1 class="card-title">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
        </div>  
        <div class="card-footer bg-transparent border-0">
            <p><a class="btn btn-primary" asp-area="" asp-page="/Index">Go Back &raquo;</a></p>
                        <p class="card-text text-wrap" style="width:auto">Acumatica Cloud ERP has a comprehensive implementation of Open Apis. <br />See below for more information.</p>

        </div>
    </div>   
</div>
<div class="container-fluid p-4 mb-2">
    <p class="text-wrap"><b>Acumatica Cloud ERP</b> provides comprehensive web services which enable integration with external systems. 
        Through the web services of Acumatica ERP, external systems can get data records from Acumatica ERP, process these records, and save new or updated records to Acumatica ERP.</P>

    <p class="text-wrap">This demo application demostrates the use of these web services, namely, the contract-based <b>re</b>presentational <b>s</b>tate <b>t</b>ransfer (ReST) APIs using the latest in <u>.NET 6.0 & ASP.NET Core</u> technologies <!--, the contract-based SOAP application programming interface (API), and the screen-based SOAP API-->. 
        The application also demonstrates how to use the <u>autogenerated RestSharp classes</u> that "wrap" the Default Web End Points available in every ERP Instance.</P>

    <p class="text-wrap">Acumatica Cloud ERP has supported Open Apis from the start. First, with the support of the SOAP protocol, then, 
        the ReST Apis as the became established in the swagger.io (now called Open Apis) community and last but not least OData v3 and v4.</p>

<p class="text-wrap">The contract-based representational state transfer (ReST) application programming interface (API) of Acumatica ERP provides the REST interface of 
    the Acumatica ERP contract-based web services, through which external systems can get data records from Acumatica ERP, process these records, 
    and save new or updated records to Acumatica ERP.For general information on the contract-based web services, see <a href="https://help-2022r1.acumatica.com/(W(1))/Help?ScreenId=ShowWiki&pageid=ff22837c-cd3a-410e-b768-88ca6e53b165">Integration Development Guide: REST API</a>.</p>
</div>
